05/01/2009
ATHENS, Greece -- Russia is conducting large-scale military exercises in the Aegean Sea, Greek media reported on Monday (January 5th). Russia's navy is training in international waters and airspace south of the Greek islands of Rhodes and Crete through January 11th, Greece's defence ministry said. This marks the first time Greece has allowed a Russian aircraft carrier to conduct naval exercises in the area. These are Russia's largest military exercises in the southern Mediterranean in ten years. (In.news, Naftemporiki, Famagusta Gazette, Kathimerini - 05/01/09; AP, Reuters - 02/01/09)
